posts.description:
AD | When it’s hair wash day & you’ve got that good lighting 💁🏼‍♀️

Thrilled to be working with @functionofbeauty on another limited edition collaboration box after so many of you loved the one we did last year! It’s genuinely been an absolute pleasure to work with them over the years as I swear by the shampoo & conditioner and my shower is never without it! There are so many things I love about the custom formulations & honestly, my hair always feels so healthy & swish!

If you want to give it a try, are on the hunt for something new or you’ve run out of your current bottles, go to functionofbeauty.com/zoesugg to get your limited edition bottles and free gift! (This comb will be your new BFF).

[Link in my bio via linktree 🙌🏼]

31 weeks ✨

Where has the time gone? Feeling pretty good in myself overall & feeling her kick about in there is just my favourite thing in the world (even when she plays my ribs like a guitar with her little tootsies)

Have also been feeling pretty overwhelmed the last few weeks. Thinking of all the things I want to get done before she’s here, things we still need to buy, people I want to see before we have her, places I want to go… not that any of that really matters but my mind is really going into overdrive! 🤯

I’m just trying to get a few small things done a day so I’m edging closer to feeling like I’m prepared but I’m starting to think even at 40 weeks you probably don’t feel that prepared?

One thing I did make a start on today was a hospital bag list, so I’d love to know what things were absolutely essential for you, for baby & for your partner or birthing companion so I don’t miss anything off! 🥰

Was going through old photos earlier and found some gems! It feels a bit different looking at them now with a little girl on the way. Will she have my curly blonde hair? Or will she have @alfiedeyes straight hair? My blue eyes? Or his big brown bush baby eyes? It’s so exciting, can’t wait to see who she will look like! Also, can we take a moment for the photos of me & @joe_sugg 😂

[ad-pr stay but no obligation to post] Had the nicest couple of days in London with @alfiedeyes. We don’t often do London with zero work commitments so it was nice to explore and relax! Thank you to the @langham_london who invited us to stay as a celebratory pre-baby staycation, we were well and truly spoiled and the hotel was incredible, I felt very lucky! Ate a lot of cake, did a spot of baby shopping & got all the room service 💕

So happy the sun is shining but wondering how skipping into the third trimester alongside summer will go hand in hand? 😂☀️🥵 Tips & advice welcome from those of you who have already done it! Haha
Currently writing this sprawled on the bed in front of two fans in my underwear with ALL windows open. It’s a sight to behold let me tell you 🙈

AD | A little day in the life reel (although definitely featuring slightly less lying down than will generally happen throughout the day 😂😅)

If, like me, you find the day runs away with you and end up scratching your head at the contents of your mostly empty fridge because you’re more of a baker than a cook, then you will LOVE the new fresh pasta kits from @lafamigliarana . They are fresh, easy & taste delicious - and as a bonus, the pasta only takes 5 minutes to cook in the microwave and is always al dente! As an avid pasta eater, these have come at the perfect time (hello instant pregnancy hunger & new born on the way) and I can tell you, having tried ALL 4 of the kits, there isn’t one I wouldn’t eat over another, they are all great! How have you found working from home & has it affected your daily routine much? #lafamigliarana

Fields of gold ☀️
Taken on iPhone & 35mm film ✨
[ad - pr stay at @wildernessreserve ] Don’t want this weekend to end! 🧡 little string of clips I’ve taken over the past few days that I popped together in a reel! Honestly had the nicest time away ☀️

My heart 🧡
Honestly, what did we ever do to deserve our furry pals?
